TERMS AND CONDITIONS

1. DEFINITIONS

   "Software" refers to the SillyTavern Character Editor and all
   associated files, documentation, and resources.

   "Non-Commercial Use" means use that is not primarily intended for
   or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

   "Cooperative Entity" means:
   - Worker cooperatives
   - Consumer cooperatives
   - Producer cooperatives
   - Multi-stakeholder cooperatives
   - Non-profit organizations
   - Educational institutions
   - Individual users for personal use

   "Commercial Entity" means any for-profit business, corporation,
   or organization that is not a Cooperative Entity.


2. GRANT OF RIGHTS

   Subject to the terms of this License, you are granted the following
   rights:

   a. COOPERATIVE ENTITIES may:
      - Use the Software for any purpose
      - Modify the Software
      - Distribute the Software
      - Distribute modified versions
      - Use the Software commercially within their cooperative structure

   b. INDIVIDUALS may:
      - Use the Software for personal, non-commercial purposes
      - Modify the Software for personal use
      - Share the Software with others under this License

   c. NON-PROFIT ORGANIZATIONS AND EDUCATIONAL INSTITUTIONS may:
      - Use the Software for their organizational purposes
      - Modify and distribute the Software
      - Use the Software in educational contexts


3. RESTRICTIONS

   a. COMMERCIAL ENTITIES are PROHIBITED from:
      - Using the Software for commercial purposes
      - Selling or licensing the Software
      - Offering the Software as part of a paid service
      - Using the Software to generate revenue
      - Incorporating the Software into commercial products

   b. ALL USERS must:
      - Retain all copyright notices
      - Include a copy of this License with distributions
      - Clearly indicate any modifications made
      - Credit the original author(s)

   c. NO WARRANTY:
      The Software is provided "AS IS" without warranty of any kind.


4. ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENTS

   When distributing the Software or modified versions, you must:

   a. Include this License file
   b. Retain all copyright and attribution notices
   c. Provide clear notice of any modifications
   d. Include a link to the original source repository
   e. Credit the original author(s) in documentation


5. COOPERATIVE EXCEPTION

   Worker cooperatives and other democratic, member-owned organizations
   may use this Software commercially, provided that:

   a. The organization is structured as a genuine cooperative where:
      - Workers/members have democratic control
      - Profits are shared equitably among members
      - The organization operates on cooperative principles

   b. The organization notifies the copyright holder of their use
      (optional but appreciated)


6. PATENT GRANT

   Each contributor grants you a non-exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free
   patent license under the contributor's essential patent claims, to
   make, use, sell, offer for sale, import and otherwise run, modify
   and propagate the contents of the Software.


7. DISCLAIMER OF WARRANTY

   THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND,
   EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF
   MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT.


8. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY

   IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS OR COPYRIGHT HOLDERS BE LIABLE FOR ANY
   CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY, WHETHER IN AN ACTION OF CONTRACT,
   TORT OR OTHERWISE, ARISING FROM, OUT OF OR IN CONNECTION WITH THE
   SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.


9. TERMINATION

   This License automatically terminates if you fail to comply with its
   terms. Upon termination, you must cease all use and distribution of
   the Software.


10. MISCELLANEOUS

    a. This License represents the complete agreement concerning the
